<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[120,1224,1431,1756]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
DIAGNOSIS: Externally distinctive, body dark brown, frons reddish brown, thorax with “ochre pollinosity,” tergites with dark posterior bands; arista with 3-2 dorsal-ventral branches, one pair of prescutellars. Terminalia: surstylus with 8–9 prensiseta pegs; hypandrium trapezoidal; distiphallus thick, length&gt; 0.5× that of aedeagal shaft; oviscapt with 18–20 pegs; spermatheca similar to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[420,534,1580,1606]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bromeliae">
<emphasis box="[420,534,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">bromeliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pavan and Cunha" authorityYear="1947" box="[602,749,1580,1606]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bromelioides">
<emphasis box="[602,749,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">bromelioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, height approximately equal to width, introvert about 0.5× capsule height.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
